cs.IT, cs.NI, cs.CR, cs.MM, cs.SY 

This paper deals with the problem of achieving secure communication in a multi-user MIMO network. It involves techniques from information theory (cs.IT) for maximizing the secrecy rate, networking (cs.NI) for scheduling transmissions, cryptography (cs.CR) for ensuring confidentiality, signal processing (cs.MM) for MIMO precoding and zero-forcing, and control systems (cs.SY) for self-interference suppression. Therefore, these are the most likely arXiv CS sub-categories for this paper.
